HMD Global has launched two new Nokia smartphones – the Nokia 6.2 and Nokia 7.2. Both smartphones target the mid-range market while offering impressive features, including powerful cameras and AI-powered battery efficiency. “Our mid-range portfolio has always been acknowledged for exceeding fan’s expectations,” said HMD Global Chief Product Officer Juho Sarvikas. “Both the Nokia 7.2 and Nokia 6.2 carry the same philosophy of delivering premium experiences at exceptional value.” Sarvikas added that both smartphones are Android 10-ready, but will ship with Android 9. The Nokia 6.2 is the first Series 6 smartphone to offer users a triple camera system, and will also support HDR. The camera is capable of shooting 4K video, and boasts an 8MP ultra-wide sensor for landscape photography opportunities. The Nokia 7.2 also boasts a triple camera system, including an impressive 48MP primary camera. HMD Global also claims that the Nokia 7.2’s camera will be the first in the smartphone industry to offer “DSLR level pro-bokeh styles.” The Nokia 6.2 is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 636 chip, while the Nokia 7.2 uses an improved Snapdragon 660 processor. Both smartphones use 3,500mAh batteries which include AI-assisted power saving technology. The Nokia 6.2 offers up to 4GB RAM, while the 7.2 offers up to 6GB, while both smartphones offer up to 128GB storage space. An additional 512GB storage via MicroSD can be added, too. The Nokia 7.2 will launch before the end of September, while the Nokia 6.2 will go on sale from mid-October. The following prices have been provided by HMD Global: Local pricing has not yet been made available for either smartphone. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-319003 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/nokia_6_2-front_back-ice-640x430.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/nokia_6_2-front_back-ice-640x430.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-conte